		<h2 id="PrvH2">Color Values</h2>
		
		<p>HTML Colors are defined using a hexadecimal (hex) notation for the combination of Red, Green, and Blue color values(RGB). The lowest value that can<br>
		be given to one of the light sources is 0(hex 00). The highest value is 255(hex FF). Hex values are written as 3 double digit numbers, starting with a #<br>
		sign.</p>
		
		<h2 id="VtorH2">16 Millions Different Colors</h2>
		
		<p>The combination of Red, Green and blue values fo 0 to 255 gives a total of no more than 16 million different colors to play with (256x256x256). Most <br>
		modern monitors are capable of displaying at least 16384 different colors. If you look at th color table below, you will see the result of varying the red<br>
		light from 0 to 255, while keeping the green and blue light at zero.</p>
		<!--In order to create TABLE in HTML you need the tag <table></table> . The attribute border is used to define the border of the table -->
		<table border ="1">
		<-- Tags <tr></tr> and <td></td> are utilized to show the value of a cell in specific row in HTML -->
      <tr>
				<td><b>Red Light</b></td>
				<td><b>Color HEX</b></td>
				<td><b>Color RGB</b></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td style="background-color:#000000"></td>
				<td>#000000</td>
				<td>rgb(0,0,0)</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td style="background-color:#400000"></td>
				<td>#400000</td>
				<td>rgb(64,0,0)</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td style="background-color:#800000"></td>
				<td>#800000</td>
				<td>rgb(128,0,0)</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td style="background-color:#C00000"></td>
				<td>#C00000</td>
				<td>rgb(192,0,0)</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td style="background-color:#FF0000"></td>
				<td>#FF0000</td>
				<td>rgb(256,0,0)</td>
			</tr>

			</table>
		
		<h2 id="TretH2">Shades of Gray</h2>
		
		<p>Gray colors are displayed using an equal amount of ower to all of the light sources. To make it easier for you to select the right gray color we have<br>
		compiled a table of gray shades for you:</p>
